<item>
            <title>[LU-18659] add new &apos;lfs projectadd&apos; command to add project entries to the /etc/projid file</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18659</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A new &lt;tt&gt;&quot;lfs projectadd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; would be useful to be able to quickly add project entries to the &lt;tt&gt;/etc/projid&lt;/tt&gt; file, which would work like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;useradd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;groupadd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should check for the existing projname and projid in the file before allowing the new entry to be added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should use the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;del&gt;c|&lt;/del&gt;&lt;del&gt;comment&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option the same as &quot;&lt;tt&gt;useradd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;/del&gt;-projid&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to match other &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; commands.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be good to also have an alias &quot;&lt;tt&gt;projadd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to keep it closer to the other commands in length.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
